name: Dustwallow Keys
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: The sands are rich with gold, but all of it is under Centaur control. This region is densely populated; be prepared for a bloody struggle.

name: Divide and Conquer
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Trolls and Golems control this beautiful forest. Expand quickly, and stain the river with the blood of your enemies.

name: Ice Crown
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: These frozen woods are haunted by souls in torment, enslaved by the dark magic of the Undead. End their suffering.

name: Booty Bay
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Pirates once anchored their ships in these quiet coves. Now the area is overrun with more brutal tenants. Establish your own kingdom on these islands before your opponent does.

name: Harrow
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: The first snowfall has come, and resources are limited. There's no time to waste.

name: Hills of Glory
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Unsavory creatures inhabit these verdant hills. The coasts are guarded by a set of twin Red Dragons who discovered long ago that the incoming ships made delicious and regular meals.

name: Ogre Mound
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: These islands are rich with gold, but the treasure is controlled by Ogres.

name: Plunder Isle
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: So far the Ogres have managed to hold off the Gnolls and hoard the richest resources. Crush both their races, as well as your opponent, beneath your heel.

name: Forestwalk
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Ragged cobwebs hang from the trees; clearly Spiders are the dominant race here. Demon bile has scarred the earth and twisted these creatures almost beyond recognition.

name: Isle of Dread
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Having allied with a trio of Bronze Dragons, the Centaur are the uncontested rulers of this island. Build up a reasonable force before you pick a fight.

name: Nighthaven
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Once a temple dedicated to light and life, this area is now a swamp littered with rocks and thorny vines. The air is thick with the miasma of disease. Raze the trees to reach your opponents.

name: Adrenaline
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Hack your way through the trees to expand and get at your opponents, but be wary. Rumor has it that in ages past, a Red Dragon made this land her home.

name: Borderlands
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: This shadowed forest is thick with Dark Trolls, who make tasty treats for the powerful scaled beasts that hold the central hill. Level the trees to reach your enemies.

name: Deadlock
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: The easiest expansions to claim are often the most difficult to keep.

name: Deadwater Drop
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Gold is plentiful in this wooded place, but so is competition. Stake your claim to the sacred Fountain of the Nightcrawlers.

name: Dragon Mountain
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Dragons have laid claim to these hills. Team up to claim their treasure; otherwise, you won't stand a chance.

name: Duskwood
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: The green of their scales is difficult to spot in the thick undergrowth, but don't underestimate the beasts that dominate this jungle. Be prepared for a fierce fight.

name: Frostsabre
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: It's said this island's Dragons will offer their assistance to any bold enough to prove their worthiness. Its also rumored their breath is colder than the grave.

name: Harvest Moon
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Expand quickly and fight your way to the center to defeat the Ogres and win vast wealth.

name: Heart to Heart
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: An Orc warrior died here while protecting the woman he loved. Both their names have been forgotten, but the powerful magic of his sacrifice reshaped the land into a lasting tribute to her.

name: Legends
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Rich with resources and treasure, these forests would make an excellent foundation on which to build an empire.

name: Lost Temple
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Ringed by gold mines, the Fountain of Health beckons. Expand quickly or risk being crushed by your opponents.

name: Mystic Isles
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Time and the ocean have ravaged these islands. Soon even their magical Way Gates will be replaced by an expanse of endless blue.

name: Tranquil Paths
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Disturb the tranquility of these lands at your own peril. Beyond the rivers lies great wealth.

name: The Glaive
author: Blizzard Enterainment
description: Only one intrepid Goblin Merchant has ever dared to set up business on this island, and business hasn't been so good since a group of Dragons decided he had a choice location.

name: Dark Forest
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Drive the invaders from these ancient lands. Be wary of the soulless guardians of stone; their treasure troves could turn the tide of war.

name: Dragon Fire
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: It's unseasonably warm for autumn, and the stench of sulfur is in the air. Clearly Dragons inhabit these dusty plains.

name: Drywater Gulch
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Lightning flashes nearby, but the sky is cloudless. The harsh sun and barren landscape have toughened this land's residents into formidable opponents.

name: Gnoll Wood
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Prepare your defenses quickly; the enemy draws near. Be careful when scouting the river's edge; Golems are lurking in the hills.

name: Moonglade
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: So far untouched by the Legion's corruption, these marshlands are inhabited by a tribe of Furbolgs who do not welcome interlopers.

name: Scorched Basin
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: As vicious as they are lovely, Harpies have begun moving onto these sands, vying with the Centaur and Razormanes for resources.

name: Stromguarde
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: This city is controlled by a pack of Bandits and Wizards. Entering it at night could be fatal if you don't keep your eyes open.

name: Swamp of Sorrows
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: A tribe of Furbolgs is stubbornly holding its own against the foul creatures invading this swamp. It's unlikely they'll last much longer, though.

name: Timbermaw Hold
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Centuries ago, Dragons abandoned this place when it was overrun by Satyrs. Wade the shallows and reclaim the land.

name: Battleground
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: The icy chill of winter has begun to fall on these war-torn lands. Gather what gold you can now, for the season of frost is fast approaching.

name: Blasted Lands
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: The barrens are littered with gold mines and heavily populated with Centaur. Team up, and don't bother leaving your base until you're prepared for a bloody conflict.

name: Bloodvenom Falls
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Darkness has invaded this swamp; even the Treants have been warped by its influence. You're going to need your allies' help.

name: Garden of War
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Team up, or be ready for a serious challenge. Squads of hostile creatures have these woods in a stranglehold, and Ogres hoard the central gold mines.

name: Golems in the Mist
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Ally with a partner to defeat your enemies. Both riches and danger await those who explore deep into the forest.

name: Petrified Forest
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Satyrs have wiped out most of this island's residents so as to control its vast wealth. Only two Mercenary Camps still offer their services, and they haven't seen much profit lately.

name: Plaguelands
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Coordinate your attacks with your allies, or you'll stand little chance. Use the nearest Way Gates to scout your enemies before they find you.

name: Plains of Snow
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: This arctic land is starkly beautiful, but merciless as well. It's unlikely anything could survive this brutal weather without a thick coat of fur--or the aid of magic.

name: Rich Man's Garden
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: A very rich man owns these gardens.  Steal his money - if you can.

name: The Crucible
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Ready to prey on the unwary, Bandits lurk in the shadows. This rich forest shelters two Fountains that glow with magic.

name: Riverrun
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Seeking the Burning Legion's favor, Satyrs have secured most of the bridges on these islands. Dare to achieve what they did not.

name: Raging Stream
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: This city is tightly packed with resources, but long ago, a flood killed most of its citizens. Coordinate with your allies, and be the first team to brave the rapids.

name: Emerald Gardens
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Lush greenery has almost succeeded in cloaking the ruins of a city whose name has passed into memory. Pay heed to its mute testimony: peace is fragile where resources are in demand.

name: Bandit Ridge
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: The cobbled road that cuts through this bandit-infested ridge is perilous and unsafe for travel. Restless thieves prowl in the night, paying their Ogre and Troll allies with the heads of foolhardy adventurers.

name: Circumvention
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: This lake is the only water supply for miles. Mercenary Heroes have moved into the area to take advantage of the constant bloodshed. Wade into the glittering shallows at your own risk.

name: Echo Isles
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Though these islands are surrounded by deep and treacherous waters, they have seen little peace. Many of the creatures dwelling here are refugees from the war. They have nothing left to lose. Don't expect a warm welcome.

name: Glacial Thaw
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Winter has reigned undisputed over this city ever since the Lich King's arrival. Now, at last, the ice has begun to melt.

name: Justice
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: The Cult of the Damned was known for massacring remote villages to supply their ghoulish experiments with innocents. With aerial support you can send the lieutenants of their latest raid back to Hell.

name: Korea
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Challenge your enemy on the chosen ground of this country. From farmland to high ground, you will battle for supremacy.

name: Melting Valley
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: After a large snowstorm the snow began to melt and left the valley inundated. Therefore, murlocs have settled here, and they want to claim the treasures of the ogres, gnolls, and trolls. Now it's your turn to thaw your mind while exploring the area, and I hope your skills are not frozen.

name: Plunder Isle LV
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: So far the Ogres have managed to hold off the Gnolls and hoard the richest resources. Crush both their races, as well as your opponent, beneath your heel.

name: Road to Stratholme
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Once a bustling trade route, this path has become a rain-sodden swampland infested with brigands and kobold mongrels. Gain a foothold and capture the strategic center.

name: Road to Stratholme LV
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Once a bustling trade route, this path has become a rain-sodden swampland infested with brigands and kobold mongrels. Gain a foothold and capture the strategic center.

name: Secret Valley
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Since ages past, there is a story told in the taverns about a secret, flooded valley where shallow water can become the grave of the incautious.

name: Shrine of the Ancients
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: There once existed a shrine to the ancient gods of yore, but all that remains is a ruin of rubble, sand, and ore. Though legends persist of creatures from the sea, that have surfaced to guard the treasures of an era long before.

name: Terenas Stand
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: "Noble countrymen, evil is upon us. Darkness has befallen our shores. Rise and slay thy enemies strike, strike so others shall live. The meek shall not fade into the night live my brethren, live. King Terenas

name: Terenas Stand LV
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: "Noble countrymen, evil is upon us. Darkness has befallen our shores. Rise and slay thy enemies strike, strike so others shall live. The meek shall not fade into the night live my brethren, live. King Terenas

name: The Two Rivers
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Separated from your enemy by two narrow bridges, you might find a Goblin Zeppelin useful in fending off attacks or dropping off a raiding party.

name: The Two Rivers LV
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Separated from your enemy by two narrow bridges, you might find a Goblin Zeppelin useful in fending off attacks or dropping off a raiding party.

name: Tirisfal Glades
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Restless servants of the Undead linger to the east and west, but the rain has washed most of these glades clean of the Scourge's taint.

name: Tirisfal Glades LV
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Restless servants of the Undead linger to the east and west, but the rain has washed most of these glades clean of the Scourge's taint.

name: Adrenaline
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Hack your way through the trees to expand and get at your opponents, but be wary. Rumor has it that in ages past, a Red Dragon made this land her home.

name: Avalanche
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Vie for supremacy, north versus south, amidst the snow-capped peaks of Lordaeron. Thirsty? Then hurry. Each team has its own Fountain, but the Taverns are first come, first served.

name: Avalanche LV
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Vie for supremacy, north versus south, amidst the snow-capped peaks of Lordaeron. Thirsty? Then hurry. Each team has its own Fountain, but the Taverns are first come, first served.

name: Bridge Too Near
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Four islands have been linked to a central landmass, thanks to clever engineering. Cross the sturdy wooden bridges to invade enemy towns, but be sure to protect your own bridges in the meantime.

name: Bridge Too Near LV
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Four islands have been linked to a central landmass, thanks to clever engineering. Cross the sturdy wooden bridges to invade enemy towns, but be sure to protect your own bridges in the meantime.

name: Broken Shard
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: In the center of this arctic area is a Tavern that hires out mercenary Heroes. With their assistance, you might gain an edge over your enemies.

name: Brutal Winter
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: The unforgiving winter is upon us a time when resources are scarce and flanks exposed. Call forth the warriors, for there could not be a better time to attack than now.

name: Centaur Grove
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: The centaur tenaciously defend these meadows, which are believed to be holy. Mystical waygates provide a quick way to travel across the land.

name: Cold Heart
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: In the arctic cold, hunger and bitterness have driven many individuals to desperate measures. Every loyalty has a price. Keep a steady supply of gold at hand.

name: Deadfall
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: For years the mages of Moonbrook have debated, "If a brave warrior falls in a forest with no one to hear it, then does it make a sound?"

name: Deathrose
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: The Deathrose is a rare flower that grows only in the deepest, darkest swamps of Ashenvale. In the hands of a master alchemist, the petals of the flower can be used to create some of the deadliest poisons known to exist in all Azeroth.

name: Desert Strife
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Each player starts on a high bluff, and can only reach other players by using a Goblin Zeppelin. As a result, Goblins in this region are more annoyingly prosperous than ever.

name: Devil's Cauldron
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: There is no escape from the searing heat. Many dark things thrive in this sulfurous environment, but it's unlikely you will. Seek out the Fountains of Health, or hire your own monstrous allies.

name: Duskwood LV
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: The green of their scales is difficult to spot in the thick undergrowth, but don't underestimate the beasts that dominate this jungle. Be prepared for a fierce fight.

name: Excavation Site
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: With the help of Gazlowe's engineers, an unexplored city was recently excavated near Durotan. Quickly secure the gold mines in the center before your enemies do.

name: Floodplains
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Follow the streams to your enemy's town, but beware. There are Ogres in the gully.

name: Floodplains 1v1 Version
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Follow the streams to your enemy's town, but beware. There are Ogres in the gully.

name: Floodplains 1v1 LV
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Follow the streams to your enemy's town, but beware. There are Ogres in the gully.

name: Frozen Clover
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: The four-leaf clover is seen as an omen of good luck. Venture into this clover's heart too soon, though, and all the luck in the world will avail you nothing.

name: Frozen Clover LV
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: The four-leaf clover is seen as an omen of good luck. Venture into this clover's heart too soon, though, and all the luck in the world will avail you nothing.

name: Goldshire
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: War and hunger have brought interlopers to Elwynn Forest, endangering the town of Goldshire. Sweep the woods free of this threat so that masons can begin laying the foundation of Stormwind.

name: Hail Stone
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Amidst these snowy pines, an enterprising band of Goblins is capitalizing on this region's conflict. Swallow your scruples, and make haste. To them, your opponents' gold is just as welcome as your own.

name: Hearthglen Hills
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Once a thriving mining region, Hearthglen Hills is now overrun with vile creatures who scrounge for what little gold remains.

name: Hellfire
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Shattered beyond repair by powerful magics, the Orc homeland is a landscape of broken dreams and despair. Only those with an iron will can overcome the armies of Hellfire.

name: Ice Flow
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Thanks to their brawny allies, the Ice Trolls have ruled this arctic land, undisputed, far too long. Secure in their power, they have grown careless and soft. They are ripe for conquest.

name: Ice Forge
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: In the frozen tundra, dark powers and magical weapons were forged upon the cold, perilous lands of Ice Forge.

name: Islands
author: Blizzard Entertaiment
description: A great civilization once inhabited this sunny archipelago. Now its shipyards are overrun by Mur'gul, and other even more precious resources are guarded by a massive Dragon Turtle and her offspring.

name: Lost Temple
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Ringed by gold mines, the Fountain of Health beckons. Expand quickly or risk being crushed by your opponents.

name: Lost Temple LV
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Ringed by gold mines, the Fountain of Health beckons. Expand quickly or risk being crushed by your opponents.

name: Paradise Islands
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: This verdant paradise is as plentiful in resources as it is in foes. Enter the shallows with a solid fighting force. Beware the spellcasters who hold the temple ruins.

name: Phantom Grove
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: An ancient horror lurks in these twisting paths turning away all but the most stalwart of champions. These would-be heroes enter confidently, seeking battle and adventure to immortalize their legacy... but none have returned.

name: Phantom Grove LV
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: An ancient horror lurks in these twisting paths turning away all but the most stalwart of champions. These would-be heroes enter confidently, seeking battle and adventure to immortalize their legacy... but none have returned.

name: Predators
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Over the millennium, many hard-won battles have assured a place where fallen generals and countless soldiers of history watch over this land forever.

name: Roundabout
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Sharp ridges of rock pierce the sky, offset by pools born from underground hot springs. The main path winds around such obstacles, but keep an eye out to avoid getting run down by an enemy.

name: Ruins
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Despite the city's age, its beauty has not yet been entirely reduced to rubble. Dotted with trees and paved in decorative tile, it can still be reclaimed from the wilderness.

name: Stone Cold Mountain
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: The blizzard that once made the high crags of Stone Cold Mountain inaccessible has finally subsided. Rumor has it that the first expeditionary force sent to explore the area returned battered and broken. Time, it seems, has only made the mountain deadlier.

name: Tanaris
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: This once-quiet peninsula is now inhabited by packs of Centaur and Razormanes. To the east and west lie enchanted Fountains; to the north and south, Goblin technology that may prove handy.

name: Tidewater Glades
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: These lush glades contain many treasures, but also dangers. Be careful not to be caught off-guard while admiring the view because your opponent might ambush your party.

name: Tidewater Glades LV
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: These lush glades contain many treasures, but also dangers. Be careful not to be caught off-guard while admiring the view because your opponent might ambush your party.

name: Turtle Rock
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Once an island for all those who were exiled, this has now become an island of riches for those who seek its hidden treasures.

name: Twisted Meadows
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: The path twists, and the future is uncertain. Race for the center and the treasures it might hold, or visit a Goblin Laboratory and explore one of the small islands.

name: Venetia
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Renegade spellcasters restrict all trade here, secure in the power of their magic. Outside the city walls, pitiless enemies greet the unwary.

name: Wetlands
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Fed by crystalline waterfalls, the jungle has devoured all but a few bricks of what was once a thriving metropolis. Take advantage of what the current denizens have to offer.

name: Whirlwind
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: A group of Owlbears has established a monopoly on providing mercenaries in this region. Meanwhile, Goblin Merchants remain on the sidelines of the fray and rake in a tidy profit.

name: Windy Waste
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Teams must defend a single ramp and a Way Gate that provides easy access for invaders. The key lies not in defense, but in controlling the Wastes.

name: Andorhal
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Stone bridges provide passage over this city's canals. Thanks to the local Goblin Laboratories, though, a quicker method of transport is available.

name: Bloodstone Mesa
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: There is no water as far as the eye can see. During the day, beneath the unforgiving sun, it's a struggle to survive. One Tavern is open for business; its mercenaries may tip the scales in your favor.

name: Bloodstone Mesa LV
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: There is no water as far as the eye can see. During the day, beneath the unforgiving sun, it's a struggle to survive. One Tavern is open for business; its mercenaries may tip the scales in your favor.

name: Copper Canyon
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Devastated by clashing armies and their blistering waves of magic, this wasteland's only remaining value is as a strategic chokehold. In the right hands, it will turn the tides of war.

name: Demon's Crossing
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: The most loathsome and malevolent of creatures have settled here. Sleepless malice keeps them locked in eternal conflict, so that even the river stinks of death.

name: Dragonblight
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Those who have braved the chill wind speak of a graveyard called Dragonblight. Treasure is rumored to lie beneath draconian bones, but vigilant dragons watch this sacred ground for foolhardy graverobbers.

name: Duststorm
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: These barren wastes hold nothing for the living, harboring only the bones of those who have fallen to the sun bleached land. The dusty earth thus serves as a savage battleground where armies can unleash their full might unhindered.

name: Duststorm LV
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: These barren wastes hold nothing for the living, harboring only the bones of those who have fallen to the sun bleached land. The dusty earth thus serves as a savage battleground where armies can unleash their full might unhindered.

name: Emerald Shores
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Fleets sail from distant lands to loot the treasures of this ancient island.  Some even come to brave the mystic defenders of the ancient temple others know better.

name: Enakro's Way
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: When Enakro faced Tasarus, the ground was torn asunder and the valley was divided in two.

name: Everfrost
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Hidden deep within the wintry crags of Everfrost is a realm of dark Nerubian horrors, protecting their frozen crypt from those that seek gold and wealth. Only when working together can these chilling nightmares be defeated and vanquished under ice forever.

name: Gnoll Wood
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Prepare your defenses quickly; the enemy draws near. Be careful when scouting the river's edge; Golems are lurking in the hills.

name: Haven of the Damned
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Forged from the remnants of Draenor, this long-forgotten island was once a haven for outcasts. Now all that remains are relics of ancient battles and lost souls.

name: Highperch
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Highperch bestows beauty and magical powers to those brave enough to withstand savage attacks from the inhabitants who protect its secret healing waters.

name: Hinterland Raid
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Deep in the woods, you track down the enemy encampment and prepare to launch a final, decisive strike. Assemble your forces quickly: the peril is great, and time grows short.

name: Jack-o-Lantern
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Take heed while you explore these eerie lands. You may find that the dead have a distinctly odd sense of humor. Is that the gleam of polished steel, or the glitter of gold? Trick... or treat?

name: Jungle Fever
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Slowly but inexorably, this peninsula is sinking into the sea. Team up and wade into the shallows, but keep an eye out. Dangerous beasts lurk in these salty waters.

name: Monsoon
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Ogres and Trolls hold most of the local riches, but Golems maintain a sleepless vigil over the island's center.

name: Monsoon LV
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Ogres and Trolls hold most of the local riches, but Golems maintain a sleepless vigil over the island's center.

name: Moonglade
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: So far untouched by the Legion's corruption, these marshlands are inhabited by a tribe of Furbolgs who do not welcome interlopers.

name: Rice Fields
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Azeroth's bread basket has now become an endless sea of the dead as war grips this once calm farmstead.

name: River of Souls
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: This war has raged for generations. Don't be deceived by the river's clarity. Its icy waters have often run red with blood, and soon the River of Souls will feast on the fallen again.

name: Rolling Hills
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Thump... Thump... War approaches. Booming drums call the troops to death and glory. The lines are drawn, and alliances are set. Nothing will hold back the bloodshed. War is here.  Thump... Thump!

name: Ruins of Stratholme
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Stratholme was once a bastion of Alliance power but now it stands as a burning testament to the evil of the Scourge. Only the bravest of heroes would dare enter this ruined city, for the undead armies of KelThuzad still hold sway over the haunted capital.

name: Savage Storm
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Expand quickly and fight your way through the snow to purchase magical items and hire allies. You would do well to establish a base upon the heights, but their isolation alone will not save you.

name: Scorched Basin
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: As vicious as they are lovely, Harpies have begun moving onto these sands, vying with the Centaur and Razormanes for resources.

name: Silverpine Forest
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Conveniently close by, mercenary Heroes are available for hire. Among these rich resources and forested hills, you could team up with allies or strike out on your own.

name: Stranglethorn Vale
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Crumbling columns and faded statuary dot this verdant island, now thickly overgrown and populated by an unusually large number of spellcasters. Rouse their ire at your own risk.

name: Sunrock Cove
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Sunrock Cove is a famous getaway for those with a lot of gold to explore its rich area. Remember to tip your Goblin Zeppelin after he rides you to a most pleasurable victory!

name: Thunder Lake
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: A landmark for travelers, this star-shaped lake is home to the plains' toughest creatures. Not by coincidence, it's also ringed by the richest gold mines. Take them if you dare. Defend them if you can.

name: Thunder Lake LV
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: A landmark for travelers, this star-shaped lake is home to the plains' toughest creatures. Not by coincidence, it's also ringed by the richest gold mines. Take them if you dare. Defend them if you can.

name: Timbermaw Hold
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Centuries ago, Dragons abandoned this place when it was overrun by Satyrs. Wade the shallows and reclaim the land.

name: Typhoon
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Coastal fog has enshrouded this archipelago. Be wary as you pass from one island to the next: there is no telling what leviathans lie sleeping in this cold sea.

name: Upper Kingdom
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Here in the shattered kingdom of Azjol-Nerub, pillars of ice pierce the land like the teeth of an enormous beast. Perhaps recruiting an ally from the native inhabitants would be wise.

name: Wellspring
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Golems guard a sacred Fountain while Bandits hide in the shadows. Unless you are fond of pain, do not venture into the central enclosure without a powerful allied army.

name: Wheel Of Chaos
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: An invading force of Dark Trolls swept this island like a plague not too long ago. Most of the Furbolgs who once thrived here were slaughtered; the few survivors have scattered into hiding.

name: Wizard's Retreat
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Nestled in the Arathi Foothills lies the pristine resort enclave where the wizards of Dalaran retreat from the front lines to recuperate while relaxing in steamy hot mana pools.

name: Banewood Bog
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: This land is truly cursed. Rivers of poison, filled with demonic bile, eat away at the earth. Ancient wyrms, terrible and great, slumber quietly within the mire. Perhaps you know of a dragon slayer, jobless, up for hire.

name: Banewood Bog LV
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: This land is truly cursed. Rivers of poison, filled with demonic bile, eat away at the earth. Ancient wyrms, terrible and great, slumber quietly within the mire. Perhaps you know of a dragon slayer, jobless, up for hire.

name: Battleground
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: The icy chill of winter has begun to fall on these war-torn lands. Gather what gold you can now, for the season of frost is fast approaching.

name: Battleground LV
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: The icy chill of winter has begun to fall on these war-torn lands. Gather what gold you can now, for the season of frost is fast approaching.

name: Cherryville
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Cherryville holds the truth of nature... from the vines, life grows and from the sheath, death follows. Those that wield both crush all those that oppose.

name: Deadlands
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Decorated with the bones of long-dead adventurers, this desolate expanse of rock seems to have little worth fighting over. Yet the locals often lock horns over every barren inch. Join the fray if you can.

name: Deadlock
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: After a bloody deadlock that lasted three long years, the Centaur became the undisputed rulers of these wild plains. Claim as many gold mines as possible, or you will fall to the hate of your enemy.

name: Deadlock LV
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: After a bloody deadlock that lasted three long years, the Centaur became the undisputed rulers of these wild plains. Claim as many gold mines as possible, or you will fall to the hate of your enemy.

name: Deathknell
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Pockets of deep water have complicated the process of getting around in this wooded region. It may prove simpler to seek out air transportation.

name: Dragon Falls
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Deep in the Ashenvale forest is a grove under the intermittent protection of a deadly Green Dragon. Word has it this region is only safe for travel in winter... or was that summer?

name: Feralas
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Separated only by a shallow stretch of water, two teams prepare to battle it out. The forest is dense enough that you may need to chop through the trees in order to better aid your allies.

name: Feralas LV
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Separated only by a shallow stretch of water, two teams prepare to battle it out. The forest is dense enough that you may need to chop through the trees in order to better aid your allies.

name: Friends
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Revisit an old favorite: team up with an ally to build shared bases. On the central hill, magical Fountains await, but their massive guardians are highly resistant to magic.

name: Full Scale Assault
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: In these eternally contested lands, war comes and goes leaving behind death and glory. Strike strategically and fight valiantly till your foes fall and you can hear the snowflakes land on the dead. Victory, at last.

name: Garden of War
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Squads of hostile creatures have these woods in a stranglehold and the central gold mines are unguarded. Do you have the courage to stake your claim?

name: Gold Rush
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: This land is shot with veins of gold, gleaming with the promise of wealth and power. Don't be lured into complacency. Expand early and often, or you cannot hope to achieve greatness.

name: Golems in the Mist LV
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Ally with a partner to defeat your enemies. Both riches and danger await those who explore deep into the forest.

name: Hurricane Isle
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: In one of the most tumultuous and dangerous parts of the ocean lies an isle run by goblins. Their whole lot in life is to sell zeppelins to wayward seafarers whose ships were destroyed by perilous hurricanes common to these waters.

name: Last Man Standing
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Though densely populated, this land also offers rich prospects. With enough gold, you can hire additional troops. Explore the northern and southern isles, where even more powerful allies can be found.

name: Market Square
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: This city was laid out by meticulous architects. Regrettably its wide streets and simple elegance attracted the attention of a passing warlord, whose army invaded the city shortly thereafter.

name: Mur'gul Oasis
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Mur'guls have long called this wetland oasis their home, and even more dangerous creatures lurk in the marsh. Encroach on their territory with extreme caution.

name: Mur'gul Oasis LV
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Mur'guls have long called this wetland oasis their home, and even more dangerous creatures lurk in the marsh. Encroach on their territory with extreme caution.

name: Northshire
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Spellcasters and thieves control much of these ruins. Challenging them at night could result in an unpleasant surprise.

name: Northshire LV
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Spellcasters and thieves control much of these ruins. Challenging them at night could result in an unpleasant surprise.

name: Plains of Snow
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: This arctic land is starkly beautiful, but merciless as well. It's unlikely anything could survive this brutal weather without a thick coat of fur--or the aid of magic.

name: Rock Quarry
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: The Last Guardian, Medivh, once lived in this desolate place. Face the lingering magics, and silence the ghosts that haunt his former home. Beware the enclosed city: it is certain death for the unprepared.

name: Sanctuary
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Team up and risk the city's brutal inhabitants as soon as you can. The treasures they guard could easily turn the tide of battle.

name: Sanctuary LV
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Team up and risk the city's brutal inhabitants as soon as you can. The treasures they guard could easily turn the tide of battle.

name: Shamrock Reef
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: There's lush greenery in every direction, but nary a spare coin to be found. Still, with a wee bit o' luck, you and your neighbor can earn a bounty by slaying any beasties nearby.

name: Slalom
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Even this far south, Northrend has no mercy. Bitter winds slice through the thickest clothes, and cunning arctic beasts race down the slopes to prey upon unsuspecting settlers.

name: Spider Falls
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: The ocean has carved deep rivers in the land and formed what looks like a giant spider. Bridges offer one way to get around, but don't kid yourself: the best transport here is of Goblin manufacture.

name: The Crossroads
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Positioned so as to extract the maximum amount of profit, Goblin Merchants and mercenaries sell their services to the quickest bidder. Expand quickly, or you'll be overrun.

name: Twilight Ruins
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: This sunken island holds many perilous opportunities for adventurous parties to besiege and conquer their opponents.

name: Twilight Ruins LV
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: This sunken island holds many perilous opportunities for adventurous parties to besiege and conquer their opponents.

name: Round Village
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Ringed by Fountains, this forested island is not a place to explore alone. Visit the shops soon, but don't bother to take the central gold mines until you can keep them.

name: Amazonia
author: Nery
description: Welcome to the dark side of the Amazon Forest... beware!

name: Ancient Isles
author: tehscourge
description: A massive land bridge leads to your opponent, while the surrounding shallows are inhabited by many other dangerous creatures.

name: Brightwater Oasis
author: Mafe
description: A place hidden far away from any known road through the Barrens. The few orc scouts who discovered it after arriving in Kalimdor immediately recognized its value for the Horde.

name: Concealed Hill
author: Unbekannt
description: Phat loot is ready for the taking within these concealed hills. But stay on the path or be lost forever.

name: Dalaran
author: Warcraft III Battle Platform
description: Dalaran was once a prosperous city, but a group of renegades and bandits have taken control after its fall. Take up your arms and throw them out!

name: Last Refuge
author: OmGan, edit by ESL
description: The Global Warming cannot be stopped and the last survivors turnout back to the upper Lands behind. Now, even the last dry lands are flooding and the last remainings are fighting for it.

name: Northern Isles
author: Keito
description: Due to the harsh enviroments of Northrend, factions have begun seeking more suitable strongholds for their northern fleets. These isles will do nicely for any faction that can secure them.

name: Swamped Temple
author: Kai Trausenegger / Anomines
description: Scientists who were excavating a sunken temple discovered some long lost ancestral artifacts. When the greedy goblins realized what these ancient ruins were hiding, they began to flood the researcher's village and claim the sacred grounds.

name: Nomad Isles
author: Lonepair
description: Navigate through the meandering streams on Nomad Isles to defeat your opponents.

name: Fountain of Manipulation
author: Red7z7
description: A land of peace and plenty... of manip.

name: Furbolg Mountain
author: BoX forelmashi
description: Beauty has given way to the beasts  Furbolgs lurk around every bend. Survival is key to victory.

name: Greenville Woods
author: Mr.Henci
description: Villagers of Greenville left the village in a hurry, leaving all their treasures there. Various creatures, attracted by the treasures, migrated to this beautiful valley. But they didn't know, they are not the only ones...

name: Hillsbrad Creek
author: Mr.Henci
description: Peaceful lands of Hillsbrad Foothills, nearly untouched by the Scourge, will soon be torn by a conflict. Only the strongest will remain standing.

name: Synergy
author: Filmting
description: An ancient power echoes across the cerulean land. Two forces, bound in an endless struggle, united they stand. Forever shall they be in strife, an ethernal misery. Though never alone, as one cannot stand without the other, for this is Synergy.

name: Circle of Fallen Heroes
author: Xander Dorn
description: Hardly anyone knows or ever knew the path into this place of myths and legends and what secrets are still there waiting to be uncovered.

name: Guardians
author: Arrr
description: These solemn warriors once guarded an ancient relic.

name: Neon City
author: Zs.SuperCumulo
description: From the old days, twisted death 4 everyone! Neon City gave birth to Moon and Sun - the most diabolic critters to grace Azeroth.

name: Nerubian Passage
author: JaleVeliki
description: Utilize the strengths of different spawn locations and work with your team to take map control and overcome your adversaries in this ancient battlefield, located within the Nerubian Kingdom.

name: Northern Felwood
author: Mafe
description: The natural inhabitants of these lands have held their own against the Burning Legion. Still, the lands and its creatures have become a poisonous shadow of their former selves.

name: Gnoll Wood
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Prepare your defenses quickly; the enemy draws near. Be careful when scouting the river's edge; Golems are lurking in the hills.

name: Echo Isles
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Though these islands are surrounded by deep and treacherous waters, they have seen little peace. Many of the creatures dwelling here are refugees from the war. They have nothing left to lose. Don't expect a warm welcome.

name: Plunder Isle LV
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: So far the Ogres have managed to hold off the Gnolls and hoard the richest resources. Crush both their races, as well as your opponent, beneath your heel.

name: Terenas Stand LV
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: "Noble countrymen, evil is upon us. Darkness has befallen our shores. Rise and slay thy enemies strike, strike so others shall live. The meek shall not fade into the night live my brethren, live. King Terenas

name: Tirisfal Glades LV
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Restless servants of the Undead linger to the east and west, but the rain has washed most of these glades clean of the Scourge's taint.

name: Avalanche LV
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Vie for supremacy, north versus south, amidst the snow-capped peaks of Lordaeron. Thirsty? Then hurry. Each team has its own Fountain, but the Taverns are first come, first served.

name: Bridge Too Near LV
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Four islands have been linked to a central landmass, thanks to clever engineering. Cross the sturdy wooden bridges to invade enemy towns, but be sure to protect your own bridges in the meantime.

name: Duskwood LV
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: The green of their scales is difficult to spot in the thick undergrowth, but don't underestimate the beasts that dominate this jungle. Be prepared for a fierce fight.

name: Frozen Clover LV
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: The four-leaf clover is seen as an omen of good luck. Venture into this clover's heart too soon, though, and all the luck in the world will avail you nothing.

name: Lost Temple
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Ringed by gold mines, the Fountain of Health beckons. Expand quickly or risk being crushed by your opponents.

name: Phantom Grove LV
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: An ancient horror lurks in these twisting paths turning away all but the most stalwart of champions. These would-be heroes enter confidently, seeking battle and adventure to immortalize their legacy... but none have returned.

name: Tidewater Glades LV
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: These lush glades contain many treasures, but also dangers. Be careful not to be caught off-guard while admiring the view because your opponent might ambush your party.

name: Turtle Rock
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: Once an island for all those who were exiled, this has now become an island of riches for those who seek its hidden treasures.

name: Twisted Meadows
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: The path twists, and the future is uncertain. Race for the center and the treasures it might hold, or visit a Goblin Laboratory and explore one of the small islands.

name: Duststorm LV
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: These barren wastes hold nothing for the living, harboring only the bones of those who have fallen to the sun bleached land. The dusty earth thus serves as a savage battleground where armies can unleash their full might unhindered.

name: Thunder Lake LV
author: Blizzard Entertainment
description: A landmark for travelers, this star-shaped lake is home to the plains' toughest creatures. Not by coincidence, it's also ringed by the richest gold mines. Take them if you dare. Defend them if you can.

author: W3Champions - v1
description: From the old days, twisted death 4 everyone! Neon City gave birth to Moon and Sun - the most diabolic critters to grace Azeroth.

author: Knecht
description: The mountain crumbles! Some paths have been blocked by boulders, it might be in your interest to remove them... or not.

author: W3Champions - v1
description: Conveniently close by, mercenary Heroes are available for hire. Among these rich resources and forested hills, you could team up with allies or strike out on your own.

name: Tatsa's Castle Gardens
author: Red7z7
description: On the outskirts of Pandaria lies the home and gardens of Tatsa Sweetbarrow. Although revered as a fierce warrior on the battlefield, he is lesser known as a master gardener. During peaceful times he returns here to relax and tend to his craft.

name: Twilight Ruins
author: W3Champions - v1
description: This sunken island holds many perilous opportunities for adventurous parties to besiege and conquer their opponents.

name: Full Scale Assault
author: Blizzard (customized by W3C)
description: In these eternally contested lands, war comes and goes leaving behind death and glory. Strike strategically and fight valiantly till your foes fall and you can hear the snowflakes land on the dead. Victory, at last.

name: Gnoll Wood
author: Blizzard (customized by W3C)
description: Prepare your defenses quickly; the enemy draws near. Be careful when scouting the river's edge; Golems are lurking in the hills.

name: Gold Rush
author: Blizzard (customized by W3C)
description: This land is shot with veins of gold, gleaming with the promise of wealth and power. Don't be lured into complacency. Expand early and often, or you cannot hope to achieve greatness.

name: Goldshire
author: Blizzard (customized by W3C)
description: War and hunger have brought interlopers to Elwynn Forest, endangering the town of Goldshire. Sweep the woods free of this threat so that masons can begin laying the foundation of Stormwind.

name: Golems in the Mist LV
author: Blizzard (customized by W3C)
description: Ally with a partner to defeat your enemies. Both riches and danger await those who explore deep into the forest.

author: Filmting, W3Champions
description: An ancient power echoes across the cerulean land. Two forces, bound in an endless struggle, united they stand. Forever shall they be in strife, an ethernal misery. Though never alone, as one cannot stand without the other, for this is Synergy.
